{"id": "1286", "post": "<div class=\"post-1286 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-virtual-servers tag-hudsonvalleyhost-com tag-kansas-city tag-openvz\" id=\"post-1286\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/hudsonvalleyhost-5-70-384mb-openvz-vps/\" rel=\"bookmark\">HudsonValleyHost \u2013 $5.70 384MB OpenVZ VPS</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/hudsonvalleyhost-com/\" rel=\"tag\">hudsonvalleyhost.com</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/kansas-city/\" rel=\"tag\">kansas city</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/openvz/\" rel=\"tag\">openvz</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \"> September 8, 2010 @ 1:25 am, by LowEndAdmin</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><a href=\"http://www.hudsonvalleyhost.com/\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"/media/images/hudsonvalleyhost.jpg\" class=\"screenshot\" alt=\"HudsonValleyHost\"></a> Via <a href=\"http://www.webhostingtalk.com/showthread.php?t=979291\">this WHT offer</a>. <a href=\"http://www.hudsonvalleyhost.com/\"><b>HudsonValleyHost</b></a> is currently giving <b>5% off</b> life time discount with promo code <b>summervps5</b>, because they are <em>\u201ccelebrating the warm weather with a summer sale\u201d</em>. Not sure which planet Hudson Valley is, but last time I checked it\u2019s September and it would be either Fall (Northern Hemisphere) or Spring (Southern). Anyway, for <b>$5.70/month</b> after the discount you will get</p><ul><li>384MB guaranteed/1024MB burstable memory</li><li>10GB storage</li><li>5Mbps unmetered bandwidth</li><li>OpenVZ/SolusVM</li></ul><p>If you think the plan looks familiar (like <a href=\"/tag/kansas-city/\">many other providers in Kansas City</a>), they are probably reselling Virpus\u2019 products. Hudson Valley Host itself seems to be long established. Domain registered back in 2004 (although with private WHOIS + adjacent name servers). Also seem to be the same company all the way through. At least their <a href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20040610113257/www.hudsonvalleyhost.com/about.html\">about page in 2004</a> worded similar to <a href=\"http://www.hudsonvalleyhost.com/aboutus.html\">their existing one</a>.</p><p>But still the question with those VPS reseller. Why not <a href=\"http://virpus.com/\">go with the source</a> when you can get $5/month everyday-price and a better package? The same also applies to BurstNet resellers. It just does not make sense to me.</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fhudsonvalleyhost-5-70-384mb-openvz-vps%2F&amp;t=HudsonValleyHost%20-%20%245.70%20384MB%20OpenVZ%20VPS\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-facebook dpsp-no-label dpsp-first\" title=\"Share on Facebook\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=HudsonValleyHost%20-%20%245.70%20384MB%20OpenVZ%20VPS&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fhudsonvalleyhost-5-70-384mb-openvz-vps%2F&amp;via=LowEndNetwork\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-twitter dpsp-no-label\" title=